HEADWORD: Turbellaria
<hw>Tur`bel*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
dim. fr. L. <ets>turbo</ets> a whirling.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An extensive group of worms which have the body covered externally
with vibrating cilia. It includes the Rhabdoc⟦oe⟧la and Dendroc⟦oe⟧la.
Formerly, the nemerteans were also included in this group.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

